                {
                    "id": "D_p_ice_independent_of_D_p_rain",
                    "description": "D_p_ice=1e-7 m (100 nm ice particle, 10× smaller than default 1 μm). Verifies that kelvin_ice changes as expected (Kelvin factor scales as exp(1/D_p); smaller particle → larger correction) while n_MP and all RainFormation outputs remain at their default values, confirming that D_p_ice and D_p_rain are independent parameters.\n\nkelvin_ice expected from ice_physics.esm 'kelvin_effect_small_particle' test.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {"D_p_ice": 1.0e-7},
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 600.0},
